</div><div class="info-panel__citations info-panel__item"><a href="#tab-citations" class="btn btn--inverse btn--slim" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="View Citations" aria-label="View Citations"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-format_quote"></i></a></div><div class="info-panel__formats info-panel__item"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Go to purchase options" aria-label="Go to purchase options"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="link-text">Get Access</span></a></div></div></div></div></header><div data-core-nav="header" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-nav-wrapper core-container" aria-label="Article navigation"><div><button aria-controls="article_sections_menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle section navigation menu"><i class="icon-list" aria-hidden="true"></i><span>Contents</span></button><nav id="article_sections_menu" aria-label="Contents" data-core-nav="article"><ul><li><a href="#abstract">Abstract</a></li><li><a href="#core-sec-figures">Figures</a></li><li><a href="#bibliography">References</a></li></ul></nav></div><nav id="article_collateral_menu"><ul class="collateral-pill" data-core-nav="collateral"><li><a href="#core-collateral-info" aria-controls="core-collateral-info" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Information & Authors" title="Information & Authors" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-info"></i><span class="sr-only">Information & Authors</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-metrics" aria-controls="core-collateral-metrics" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Metrics & Citations" title="Metrics & Citations" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-metrics"></i><span class="sr-only">Metrics & Citations</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-controls="core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Get Access" title="Get Access" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="sr-only">Get Access</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-references" aria-controls="core-collateral-references" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="References" title="References" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-references"></i><span class="sr-only">References</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-figures" aria-controls="core-collateral-figures" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Figures" title="Figures" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-photo"></i><span class="sr-only">Figures</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-tables" aria-controls="core-collateral-tables" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Tables" title="Tables" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-table"></i><span class="sr-only">Tables</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-media" aria-controls="core-collateral-media" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Media" title="Media" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-play-circle-filled"></i><span class="sr-only">Media</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-share" aria-controls="core-collateral-share" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Share" title="Share" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-share"></i><span class="sr-only">Share</span></a></li></ul></nav></div></div><div data-core-wrapper="content"><div id="abstracts" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="abstract" property="abstract" typeof="Text" role="doc-abstract"><h2 property="name">Abstract</h2><div role="paragraph">The segmental classification of congenital heart disease, first conceptualized nearly 50 years ago, is now well established. The Van Praagh classification system, in particular, is commonly used throughout North America to facilitate communication between physicians from various specialties who are involved in diagnosing and managing congenital cardiovascular abnormalities. In the Van Praagh system, a three-part notation consisting of letters separated by commas and encompassed by a set of braces is used to succinctly describe the visceroatrial situs, the orientation of the ventricular loop, and the position and relation of the great vessels. For example, the notation “{S, D, S}” describes the normal anatomic configuration, in which the morphologic right atrium and largest hepatic lobe are on the patient’s right side and the morphologic left atrium, stomach, and spleen are on the left side (situs <i>s</i>olitus); the ventricular loop is curved rightward (<i>d</i>extro- or <span data-style="small-caps">d</span>-loop); and the aorta is posterior to and rightward of the main pulmonary artery (situs <i>s</i>olitus). Because the Van Praagh notation imposes on its users a systematic approach to anatomic description, it is a helpful device for structuring the interpretation of imaging studies as well as the reporting of results: First, the morphologic right and left atria and ventricles must be identified; next, the visceroatrial situs and ventricular loop orientation may be determined from the positions of the cardiac chambers; and last, the position and relation of the great vessels (normal, inverted, transposed, or malpositioned) can be established. The article provides concise, step-by-step guidance for applying the Van Praagh system in the radiology reading room.</div><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2013</div></section></div></div><section id="bodymatter" data-extent="bodymatter" property="articleBody" typeof="Text"><div class="core-container"><section aria-labelledby="denial-block-title" class="denial-block "><h2 id="denial-block-title" class="denial-block__title">Get full access to this article</h2><p class="denial-block__text">View all available purchase options and get full access to this article.</p><div class="denial-block__cta"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span>Get Access</span></a></div><footer class="denial-block__footer"><span>Already a Subscriber? </span><span>Sign in as an </span><a href="/action/showLogin?redirectUri=/doi/10.1148/rg.332125086">individual</a><span> or via your </span><a href="/action/ssostart?uri=/doi/10.1148/rg.332125086">institution</a></footer></section></div></section><section id="backmatter" data-extent="backmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="core-sec-figures" data-type="figures"><h2>Figures</h2><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig01a.jpeg" height="1134" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig01a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig01b.jpeg" height="1201" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig01b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig02a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1000" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig02a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig02b.jpeg" height="1160" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig02b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig02c.jpeg" height="1152" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig02c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig03a.jpeg" height="1077" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig03a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig03b.jpeg" height="1075" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig03b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig04a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig04a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig04b.jpeg" height="1280" width="1245" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig04b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig05a.jpeg" height="1266" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig05a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig05b.jpeg" height="1272" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig05b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig06.jpeg" height="1244" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig06" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6</span> Determining the visceroatrial situs. Coronal contrast-enhanced CT image of the lower thorax and upper abdomen shows that the supradiaphragmatic IVC (*) is on the patient’s left side. According to the rule of venoatrial concordance, the IVC at this level drains into the right atrium; therefore, the morphologic right atrium is on the patient’s left side. The largest lobe of the liver is also seen on the left side, whereas the stomach is on the right side, the mirror image of the normal arrangement. The appropriate classification is situs inversus, denoted as “{I, _, _}.”<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig06">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig07.jpeg" height="1004" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig07" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7</span> Identifying the ventricles. Axial contrast-enhanced cardiac CT image depicts a band of tissue (arrow) traversing the apex of a cardiac chamber and extending from the base of the papillary muscle to the septal wall. This is the moderator band, one of the features that helps identify the morphologic right ventricle.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig07">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig08a.jpeg" height="1172" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig08a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig08b.jpeg" height="1173" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig08b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig09.jpeg" height="971" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig09" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9</span> Three-dimensional cardiac CT image with a superimposed reconstruction of the right hand shows how the hand rule is used to determine the orientation of the ventricular loop. While viewing the heart from the anterior to the posterior direction, the viewer imagines placing a hand into the morphologic right ventricle with the palm against the interventricular septum (black *), the thumb in the right ventricular inflow tract (white *), and the fingers in the outflow tract (arrow). If this exercise can be performed with the right hand, a <span data-style="small-caps">d</span>-loop is present; if it can be performed only with the left hand, an <span data-style="small-caps">l</span>-loop is present.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig09">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig10.jpeg" height="1054" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig10" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10</span> Normal configuration of the great vessels. Axial contrast-enhanced cardiac CT image demonstrates situs solitus of the great vessels at the level of the valves, a configuration designated as “{_, _, S}.” The aorta (red circle, <i>A</i>) has a normal posterior relation and normal rightward position relative to the MPA (blue circle, <i>P</i>).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig10">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig11.jpeg" height="1143" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig11" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11</span> Inversion of the great vessels. Axial contrast-enhanced cardiac CT image demonstrates situs inversus of the great vessels at the level of the valves, which is designated as “{_, _, I}.” The aorta (red circle) has a normal posterior relation to the MPA (blue circle) but is positioned at its left, a mirror image of the normal configuration.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig11">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig12a.jpeg" height="631" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig12a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig12b.jpeg" height="479" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig12b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig13a.jpeg" height="906" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig13a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig13b.jpeg" height="1037" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig13b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig13c.jpeg" height="1015" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig13c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig14a.jpeg" height="1098" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig14b.jpeg" height="1110" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig14c.jpeg" height="897" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig14c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig14d.jpeg" height="902" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig14d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig14e.jpeg" height="843" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig14e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig15a.jpeg" height="596" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig15a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig15b.jpeg" height="423" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig15b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig15c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.332125086/asset/images/125086fig15c.jpeg" height="417" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 15c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.332125086&amp;id=fig15